"ma'am" before.

267
00:12:05,003 --> 00:12:06,503
Is that a big deal?

268
00:12:06,505 --> 00:12:09,472
Kind of. When was the first time
someone called you "sir"?

269
00:12:09,474 --> 00:12:10,907
Sixth grade,

270
00:12:10,909 --> 00:12:13,843
but I wore a sport coat
and carried a briefcase, so...

271
00:12:14,679 --> 00:12:17,781
Can you believe
when I met you I was 22?

272
00:12:17,783 --> 00:12:19,682
(laughs)
I mean, it's crazy!

273
00:12:19,684 --> 00:12:21,384
Where did all that time go?

274
00:12:21,386 --> 00:12:25,388
Mm, you watched
<i>The Bachelor</i> a lot.

275
00:12:25,390 --> 00:12:27,223
Yeah, go ahead and make jokes,

276
00:12:27,225 --> 00:12:28,958
but your thirties
are almost over.

277
00:12:28,960 --> 00:12:30,393
No, they're not.

278
00:12:30,395 --> 00:12:32,295
You're closer to 40
than you are 30.

279
00:12:32,297 --> 00:12:35,865
Ha, ha! You
married an old man.

280
00:12:35,867 --> 00:12:37,834
Tell you what.

281
00:12:37,836 --> 00:12:39,335
Let's do something
fun tonight.

282
00:12:39,337 --> 00:12:40,637
Won't make us any younger.

283
00:12:40,639 --> 00:12:43,273
Well, maybe not, but some
day we actually will be old,

284
00:12:43,275 --> 00:12:45,108
and we'll look
back on this night

285
00:12:45,110 --> 00:12:47,243
and remember what
a good time we had.

286
00:12:47,245 --> 00:12:49,212
Okay, like what?

287
00:12:49,214 --> 00:12:52,315
I know. Food fight!

288
00:12:57,756 --> 00:13:00,356
I'll keep thinking.

289
00:13:02,694 --> 00:13:06,096
Look, I know you both feel bad
about being alone, but sometimes

290
00:13:06,098 --> 00:13:09,499
the best thing you can do is
take a little time for yourself,

291
00:13:09,501 --> 00:13:11,968
especially when you just
got out of a relationship.

292
00:13:11,970 --> 00:13:14,204
Speaking of ending
relationships,

293
00:13:14,206 --> 00:13:18,575
when British Honduras
became Belize,

294
00:13:18,577 --> 00:13:21,311
they designed a new
flag with a tree on it,

295
00:13:21,313 --> 00:13:25,348
and I would like to hang
myself from that tree.

296
00:13:29,688 --> 00:13:32,555
But, Amy,
when you and Sheldon split up,

297
00:13:32,557 --> 00:13:34,757
didn't you start dating someone
right away?

298
00:13:34,759 --> 00:13:37,293
Well, I... I wouldn't
say right away.

299
00:13:37,295 --> 00:13:40,263
And actually, it was
three different men.

300
00:13:40,265 --> 00:13:42,132
KRIPKE:
Three different men?!

301
00:13:42,134 --> 00:13:46,870
Damn, girl,
way to give the milk away?

302
00:13:46,872 --> 00:13:49,439
Oh, looks like
we just lost Kripke.

303
00:13:49,441 --> 00:13:52,642
Actually, I'm still here.

304
00:13:52,644 --> 00:13:54,677
Now?
Yup.

305
00:13:54,679 --> 00:13:56,513
Now?
Yup!

306
00:13:56,515 --> 00:13:58,515
Now?

307
00:13:58,517 --> 00:14:02,051
Oh, looks like
we just lost Kripke.

308
00:14:02,053 --> 00:14:04,020
Before Emily,
I was alone for so long.

309
00:14:04,022 --> 00:14:06,556
I just... I don't know
if I can do that again.

310
00:14:06,558 --> 00:14:08,091
Well, you know,
here is something

311
00:14:08,093 --> 00:14:09,425
that might cheer you up.

312
00:14:09,427 --> 00:14:13,396
The flag of the Isle of Man
is nothing but three legs

313
00:14:13,398 --> 00:14:16,733
sharing a weird pair
of underpants, so...

314
00:14:16,735 --> 00:14:19,002
you think you
got problems.

315
00:14:20,505 --> 00:14:22,505
I have an idea.

316
00:14:22,507 --> 00:14:24,140
Maybe someone in our audience

317
00:14:24,142 --> 00:14:26,075
would be interested
in meeting Rajesh.

318
00:14:26,077 --> 00:14:28,077
Ladies, I can attest

319
00:14:28,079 --> 00:14:30,113
that he is a kind,
handsome, intelligent...

320
00:14:30,115 --> 00:14:32,916
KOOTHRAPPALI: Rich parents!
Don't forget, rich parents!

321
00:14:34,753 --> 00:14:37,187
...spoiled astrophysicist
who not only...

322
00:14:37,189 --> 00:14:38,755
(phone ringing)

323
00:14:38,757 --> 00:14:42,125
Oh. Well, that was quick.

324
00:14:42,127 --> 00:14:44,594
Hi. You're on
<i>Fun with Flags.</i>

325
00:14:44,596 --> 00:14:46,863
KRIPKE:
Hey, I think I got cut off.

326
00:14:49,401 --> 00:14:50,934
Hello, Kripke.

327
00:14:50,936 --> 00:14:53,136
I have a flag question.

328
00:14:53,138 --> 00:14:56,539
How many men
did you have sex with?

329
00:14:57,709 --> 00:15:00,877
Let's see. What's
young and fun?

330
00:15:00,879 --> 00:15:02,879
Uh, we could
go dancing.

331
00:15:02,881 --> 00:15:04,347
Are you actually
gonna dance?

332
00:15:04,349 --> 00:15:05,381
Of course.
Yeah.

333
00:15:05,383 --> 00:15:07,417
No one wants to see that.

334
00:15:07,419 --> 00:15:09,953
