in over ten minutes,

371
00:16:55,026 --> 00:16:58,294
so, enjoy your
new show, Internet.

372
00:16:58,296 --> 00:17:02,965
<i>Dr. Amy Farrah Flower</i>
<i>Present... With.</i>

373
00:17:05,470 --> 00:17:07,503
KOOTHRAPPALI:
I'm sorry for bothering you.

374
00:17:07,505 --> 00:17:08,938
I'll hang up now.

375
00:17:08,940 --> 00:17:10,473
No, hold on, Rajesh.

376
00:17:10,475 --> 00:17:12,375
You know, you're not being
very sympathetic.

377
00:17:12,377 --> 00:17:14,510
You know firsthand
that breakups are hard.

378
00:17:14,512 --> 00:17:16,946
Fine.

379
00:17:16,948 --> 00:17:19,615
If you insist on making
me a part of this,

380
00:17:19,617 --> 00:17:21,984
yes, I knowledge how
painful they can be.

381
00:17:21,986 --> 00:17:26,589
However, pain has an
evolutionary purpose.

382
00:17:26,591 --> 00:17:29,492
It provides information
from the environment

383
00:17:29,494 --> 00:17:32,061
that, uh, behavior
isn't good for us.

384
00:17:32,063 --> 00:17:34,530
KRIPKE: Like when I fell in love
with that stripper

385
00:17:34,532 --> 00:17:36,733
and bought her a Prius.

386
00:17:38,770 --> 00:17:41,137
I'm just gonna push
all the buttons.

387
00:17:43,041 --> 00:17:45,742
Raj, now, I'm sorry
you're suffering.

388
00:17:45,744 --> 00:17:48,945
When Amy and I were
broken up, I also suffered.

389
00:17:48,947 --> 00:17:51,314
And this may
sound surprising,

390
00:17:51,316 --> 00:17:53,683
but I'm grateful for
having gone through it.

391
00:17:53,685 --> 00:17:55,685
Really?

392
00:17:55,687 --> 00:17:57,720
Yes.

393
00:17:57,722 --> 00:18:02,091
I believe our relationship
now is stronger than ever.

394
00:18:02,093 --> 00:18:04,694
So do I.

395
00:18:04,696 --> 00:18:06,129
When-when we were apart,

396
00:18:06,131 --> 00:18:08,297
I learned how important
you are to me.

397
00:18:08,299 --> 00:18:10,466
And I realize

398
00:18:10,468 --> 00:18:13,069
that when two people are
in love, sometimes they...

